<b><it>Highway Encounter</it></b> is a computer game released on the Sinclair <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../467/34467.xml">
ZX Spectrum</link> 48K, <computer wordnetid="103082979" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../ury/22nd_century.xml">
Amstrad CPC</link></computer>
, and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../293/7293.xml">
Commodore 64</link> by <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../155/2430155.xml">
Vortex Software</link></institution>
</company>
 in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../025/1323025.xml">
1985</link>. It was written by <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<computer_user wordnetid="109951274" confidence="0.8">
<programmer wordnetid="110481268" confidence="0.8">
<engineer wordnetid="109615807" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../363/8839363.xml">
Costa Panayi</link></causal_agent>
</engineer>
</programmer>
</computer_user>
</person>
</physical_entity>
 who also coded <it>Android</it>, <it>Android 2</it>, <it><event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<social_event wordnetid="107288639" confidence="0.8">
<contest wordnetid="107456188" confidence="0.8">
<game wordnetid="100456199" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../953/3417953.xml">
TLL</link></psychological_feature>
</game>
</contest>
</social_event>
</event>
</it>, <it>Cyclone</it> and <it>Revolution</it>.<p>

<it>Highway Encounter</it> is a strategy/action game played from a 3D <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../823/167823.xml">
isometric perspective</link> in which you must successfully chaperone a bomb along a long, straight stretch of highway and into the alien base at the end of it. There are thirty screens to pass through and most are filled with hazards that threaten to block your progress (such as barrels) or destroy you (aliens and explosive mines).</p>
<p>

Players control a robotic "Vorton" (resembling a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../140/9140.xml">
dalek</link> from <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../209/8209.xml">
Doctor Who</link></series>
</it>) and one of the things that provides <it>Highway Encounter</it> with its unique appeal is that the bomb is constantly being pushed onwards by your extra lives - four more Vortons, who accompany you along the highway. It is in fact possible for all your extra lives to be lost without the player character being destroyed once.</p>
<p>

<it>Highway Encounter</it> was followed by a sequel, <it><link>
Alien Highway</link></it> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../022/1323022.xml">
1986</link>.</p>

